page.title: 07Newport Docks
page.content: On June 5th we went to{Newport Docks}. When we got there, a lady called Tracy showed us around. First we went to the lock. The one side of the lock, the water was 47 feet but the lock water was 50 feet. Then we went to the sheds where they kept the cargo from the ships. We went to see the cars, these included Mitsubushi, Subaru and Lonsdale. They came from Japan. On the way to see the cars, we saw a ship carrying bananas from Jamaica. We also saw two tug boats. The docks also handle citrus fruits from Israel. The coal in the docks is sent to France and Spain. The timber is softwood from Canada and hardwood from Malaysia.
